    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">A GP is nonparametric: instead of fitting a fixed number of weights, it uses the kernel to define a prior over the entire function space. Conditioning on data is Bayes' rule applied to function space. The kernel matrix is a metric on the input space -- connecting GPs to Leinster's magnitude theory, where the magnitude of a metric space measures its "effective size."</p>

